<li class="commentbody" id="comment-289320">
			<cite><a href='http://delicioushouse.blogspot.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Becks</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-289320" title="">May 29, 2009</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">51</div>

				<p>Sacha &#8211; I think soy flour has a really distinct NON-grainy taste that probably wouldn&#8217;t be very pleasing in a faux GF graham cracker, and that nut flours probably have the wrong texture and oiliness to get the right kind of crispiness too. I think a combination of rice flours (1/3 white, 1/3 brown, 1/3 sweet), quinoa flour, or sorghum flour would probably make much better substitutes in terms of comperable taste and texture. (sorghum is my least favorite though, it has an almost gummy texture sometimes!).</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
