<li class="commentbody" id="comment-303791">
			<cite><a href='http://superfinespot.blogspot.com/2009/07/graham-crackers-from-la-brea-bakery.html' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Sweetie</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-303791" title="">July 12, 2009</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">183</div>

				<p>Hi Deb-<br />
I made this recipe yesterday and the end result was another SK success for me. Having said that, it didn&#8217;t come together completely perfectly for me. Have you ever tried this with a standing mixer? I see from the pics you used a food processor but I used a standing mixer and I would advise against it.  Since the butter is frozen it doesn&#8217;t get cut into the flour by the paddle attachment in same way I imagine it would from a blade. So when my dough was pulled together and going into the fridge to chill overnight, I saw pretty large chunks of solid butter.  Also, this dough required more flour on the rolling surface than, say, your brownie roll out cookies (loved those!), but the baked cookies hold shape and turn out really nicely.<br />
I have more notes on my blog which I&#8217;ve linked from my name. I&#8217;ll post pics there.<br />
Thanks very much!</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
