				<p>Interesting recipe, although for it to truly be called graham cracker it should be made with graham flour, not white flour. </p>
<p>If you were planing on making a &#8220;graham cracker&#8221; crust from this recipe, why not cut a &#8220;cracker the size of your spring form pan and back it in there, then when it cools, just add the filling, no need to crush any crackers, plus you can cut back a bit on the butter and feel less guilty about having a second slice.</p>
